  "text": "Paired rod-like centrioles with the usual nine skewed triplet fibers (Fig. 12) are generally found in a depression in the nuclear surface (of also Berkaloff, ]963). Spindle fiber-like elements radiate from the lower portion of the centriole along the surface of the nucleus, but their ultimate endings are obscure (Fig. 13) . The microtubules found in close association with the wall of higher plants [CITATION_1] are apparently not present or not preserved in a similar region in these cells.",
